== another independent quibble ==
Bayesian's may insist further that we should not rest content with dispensing
with the 2 place relationship "Evidence E warrants (or makes "rationally
acceptable") belief in B" in favour of the place relationship "Evidence E
warrants confidence C in belief B". They may wish to insist that "Evidence E
warrants confidence C in belief B given priors P" is the most fundamental
relationship, and that the other accounts of the relationships between evidence
and what is justified by that evidence, insofar as they are true, are variously
vague versions of this principle.
